A Graphical user interface (GUI)  which can also be called a desktop, is a screen made of Icons that represents code. instead of knowing computer language the user can click on and icon and the computer will do what the user wants it to do. the GUI makes it very easy for every user.
Another opperating system function is  the ability to run an application, such as Word processing software. when the OS is commaned to open a application it locates the program and loads it into the primary memory. The newer and operating systems can multitask which means they can run more then one application at a time.
We all have to mannage our resources even computers. Opperating systems manage the resources of a computer such as the printer, mouse, keyboard, memory and monitor.
